**2.2 Visual Design Principles**

\*\*Immersive Mode\*\*

> • Dark theme mandatory (reduces screen glare, focuses attention)
>
> • Minimal chrome (controls appear on tap, fade when not needed)
>
> • Content area maximized
>
> • Subtle ambient animations (breathing pulses, soft glows)
>
> • No jarring transitions

\*\*Color System\*\*

:root { \--bg-session: #0a0a0a; \--text-primary: #ffffff; \--text-muted:
#666666; \--accent-arousal: #ff4d6d; /\* Pink/red for arousal indicators
\*/ \--accent-affirm: #c77dff; /\* Purple for affirmations \*/
\--accent-edge: #ff6b6b; /\* Red pulse for edge moments \*/
\--accent-calm: #4ecdc4; /\* Teal for breathe/calm \*/ \--accent-denial:
#ffd93d; /\* Gold for denial/control \*/ \--progress-fill:
linear-gradient(90deg, #ff4d6d, #c77dff); }

\*\*Typography\*\*

> • Affirmations: Large, soft serif or elegant sans (e.g., Playfair
> Display, Cormorant)
>
> • Stats/controls: Clean sans (system default or Inter)
>
> • No harsh fonts, nothing that breaks immersion

**2.3 Screen Lock & Focus Mode**

interface FocusModeConfig { screenLock: true, // Request wake lock API
orientationLock: \'portrait\', // Or \'landscape\' for video
notificationSuppression: true, // Request DND mode exitConfirmation:
true, // \"Are you sure?\" on back minimizeWarning: true, // Alert if
app backgrounded hapticOnMinimize: \'warning_pulse\' // Vibrate if
leaving }

**Part 3: Edge Tracking Interface**

**3.1 Edge Button Behavior**

\*\*Primary Edge Action\*\*

interface EdgeAction { // User taps when reaching edge onTap: () =\> {
incrementEdgeCount(); triggerHapticPulse(\'edge_reached\');
showEdgeConfirmation(); logEdgeTimestamp(); checkForAuctionTrigger();
updateIntensityDisplay(); }, // Visual feedback feedback: { haptic:
\'strong_pulse\', visual: \'ripple_expand\', audio: \'subtle_chime\', //
Optional duration: 500 // ms } }

