**Part 13: UX Principles**

> 1\. \*\*Immersion over interface\*\*: Every UI element should serve
> the session, not distract from it.
>
> 2\. \*\*Progressive disclosure\*\*: Controls appear when needed, fade
> when not.
>
> 3\. \*\*Physical feedback first\*\*: Haptics confirm actions before
> visual feedback.
>
> 4\. \*\*Unpredictability creates engagement\*\*: AI-controlled timing
> keeps the brain anticipating.
>
> 5\. \*\*Feminization woven throughout\*\*: Every affirmation, every
> content piece reinforces identity.
>
> 6\. \*\*Commitments feel binding\*\*: The auction UI should feel
> weighty, consequential.
>
> 7\. \*\*Recovery matters\*\*: Don\'t rush past recovery---it\'s part
> of the psychological architecture.
>
> 8\. \*\*Completion is ritual\*\*: The end flow should feel like
> closure, not abrupt termination.
>
> 9\. \*\*Evidence accumulates\*\*: Every session adds to the undeniable
> record.
>
> 10\. \*\*The system rewards, not punishes\*\*: Even denial should feel
> like achievement.
